The paper discusses noise-based logic and its potential for beyond-Moore-chips, which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the use of logic gates for spike-based brain logic, which falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper proposes new logic gates for Boolean logic, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the advantages and disadvantages of different types of logic, which falls under the category of Architecture (cs.AR) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
